AIM:

To add exception handling and validation to the RESTful Spring Boot application. Implement global exception handling and apply validation annotations to ensure correct input data and return meaningful error responses.

PROCEDURE:

Open the existing Spring Boot RESTful application.

Add the dependency Spring Boot Starter Validation in the project.

Modify the Entity class and apply validation annotations such as:

@NotNull
@NotBlank
@Size
@Min

Create a Custom Exception class (for example: ResourceNotFoundException).

Create a Global Exception Handler using @ControllerAdvice.

Handle the following exceptions:

Resource not found
Validation errors
General exceptions

Update the Controller class and use @Valid annotation in request body.

Run the application and test invalid inputs using Postman.

Verify that the application returns proper error messages in JSON format.

